cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks to detect and predict injuries in MLB pitchers from video data. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of video data also suggests the possibility of multimedia (cs.MM) being a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of injuries on fan interest, which could be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
